✅ Cosmos SQL (copy-paste)

If agency is an object (your latest screenshots show this):

SELECT
  /* name candidates as scalars */
  (SELECT VALUE CONCAT(n.lastName, " ", n.firstName)
     FROM n IN c.name
     WHERE n.charactersetType = "kanji"
       AND IS_DEFINED(n.lastName)  AND n.lastName  IS NOT NULL
       AND IS_DEFINED(n.firstName) AND n.firstName IS NOT NULL
     OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1) AS kanjiName,

  (SELECT VALUE CONCAT(n.lastName, " ", n.firstName)
     FROM n IN c.name
     WHERE n.charactersetType = "kana"
       AND IS_DEFINED(n.lastName)  AND n.lastName  IS NOT NULL
       AND IS_DEFINED(n.firstName) AND n.firstName IS NOT NULL
     OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1) AS kanaName,

  (SELECT VALUE CONCAT(n.lastName, " ", n.firstName)
     FROM n IN c.name
     WHERE n.charactersetType = "alphabet"
       AND IS_DEFINED(n.lastName)  AND n.lastName  IS NOT NULL
       AND IS_DEFINED(n.firstName) AND n.firstName IS NOT NULL
     OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1) AS alphabetName,

  /* first validated email (scalar) */
  (SELECT VALUE e.address
     FROM e IN c.eMail
     WHERE e.addressValidated = true
       AND IS_DEFINED(e.address) AND e.address IS NOT NULL AND e.address != ""
     OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1) AS email,

  /* first landline phone (object) */
  (SELECT VALUE p
     FROM p IN c.phoneNumber
     WHERE p.type = "landline"
       AND IS_DEFINED(p.number1) AND p.number1 IS NOT NULL AND p.number1 != ""
     OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1) AS phoneObj,

  /* agency scalars */
  c.agency.agencyName   AS agencyName,
  c.agency.agencyNumber AS agencyNumber

FROM c
WHERE c.agentId = @agentId

If agency is an array in your collection, use this line instead of the two agency lines above:

(SELECT VALUE a FROM a IN c.agency OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1) AS agencyObj

…and then map agencyObj.name, agencyObj.agencyNumber in outputs.

