✅ Do you need extractor changes?

No changes required if you use the JSON above:
	•	Outputs are simple dot paths (e.g., phoneObj.number1) → your resolver already supports this.
	•	No ?(@...) filters, no advanced JsonPath.
	•	Arrays are handled inside SQL, so outputs are scalars or simple objects.

Optional tiny improvement (not required): if you want extra safety when a projected field accidentally comes back as a single-element array, you can add the “auto-unwrap one-element array” line in your extractOutputs():

if (valueNode != null && valueNode.isArray() && valueNode.size() == 1) {
    valueNode = valueNode.get(0);
}


